BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.2 Td (The last wisp of Owen's shadow disappeared completely on a Tuesday in March.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 676.2 Td (He was helping a younger kid who had been caught lying. 'I used to lie all the time,' Owen) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 662.2 Td (told him. 'I know how it feels.') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 648.2 Td ('Doesn't the truth ever scare you?' the little boy asked.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 634.2 Td ('Every single day,' Owen admitted. 'But I'll tell you a secret: the truth is like a) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 620.2 Td (muscle. The more you use it, the stronger it gets. And the lies? They're like sugar  ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 606.2 Td (sweet in the moment but they make you sick.') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 592.2 Td (As he said those words, the last shadow puff dissolved into nothing. Owen was finally,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 578.2 Td (completely free.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 554.4 Td ([Illustration: Owen talking to a younger boy on the playground, the final tiny wisp of) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 540.4 Td (shadow dissolving into sunshine, Owen looking completely free and light, a full-circle) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 526.4 Td (moment]) Tj ET
